Ed, I see by the sun
it's time for you to hibernate again.

841
01:07:17,338 --> 01:07:19,923
You're right, I suppose.
I guess it is childish...

842
01:07:19,923 --> 01:07:22,343
...but when I was about 18...

843
01:07:23,427 --> 01:07:27,348
...and my dad and I couldn't
communicate about anything at all...

844
01:07:27,931 --> 01:07:30,601
...we could still talk about baseball.

845
01:07:31,727 --> 01:07:33,604
Now that was real.

846
01:07:38,692 --> 01:07:41,320
You know what the secret of life is?

847
01:07:41,362 --> 01:07:42,905
It's this.

848
01:07:44,448 --> 01:07:46,659
One thing.
Just one thing.

849
01:07:48,243 --> 01:07:50,913
- And what's that?
- I have no idea.

850
01:07:51,747 --> 01:07:54,249
But ask Curly cos he seems to know.

851
01:07:54,249 --> 01:07:57,127
- Curly knows the secret of life?
- Yeah.

852
01:07:57,753 --> 01:08:00,464
I'm gonna invite him over.
He's a very interesting guy.

853
01:08:00,464 --> 01:08:02,216
I'm sure he is.

854
01:08:08,973 --> 01:08:10,557
Hey, Curly.

855
01:08:11,558 --> 01:08:13,936
Curly?
Curl, you got a minute?

856
01:08:16,063 --> 01:08:21,443
He is a real cowboy. He sleeps with his
eyes open so he can still watch the herd.

857
01:08:24,488 --> 01:08:26,115
