All right, listen up. Ben, I want you
to take the left flank with TR and Bonnie.

877
01:10:01,585 --> 01:10:04,088
I want you three boys to ride point.

878
01:10:04,088 --> 01:10:06,924
I'm gonna push with Steve, Barry and Ira.

879
01:10:06,966 --> 01:10:09,426
Yeah, they're pros.
It'll be OK.

880
01:10:34,410 --> 01:10:36,203
So long, cowboy.

881
01:10:53,846 --> 01:10:57,349
- You know, it makes you stop and think.
- Stop the clock.

882
01:10:57,349 --> 01:11:00,144
- That's 25 minutes. I win.
- Win what?

883
01:11:00,853 --> 01:11:04,773
I had under a half an hour
before you started to talk about death.

884
01:11:04,857 --> 01:11:07,359
Why would you think
I would talk about death?

885
01:11:07,359 --> 01:11:11,071
We just came from a funeral.
And it's your favourite subject.

886
01:11:11,363 --> 01:11:13,782
It is not. I think
when you see a life end...

887
01:11:13,782 --> 01:11:16,785
...it's a natural time to think
about your own mortality.

888
01:11:16,785 --> 01:11:19,496
No, it isn't.
Why do that to yourself?

889
01:11:19,788 --> 01:11:22,291
When somebody dies,
I don't change places with him.

890
01:11:22,291 --> 01:11:24,793
I appreciate the fact that I'm not dead.

891
01:11:24,793 --> 01:11:28,297
Look at this. It's a beautiful day.
I'm here with my best friends.

892
01:11:28,297 --> 01:11:31,050
We're driving a herd of cattle
across the plains.

893
01:11:31,050 --> 01:11:34,595
Pretty goddamn great.
It's one of the best days of my life.

894
01:11:34,595 --> 01:11:37,598
All right. What is the best day of your life?

895
01:11:37,640 --> 01:11:41,226
- You mean ever?
- Yeah. Best day ever in your whole life.

896
01:11:41,644 --> 01:11:45,272
And you can't do when your kids
were born. That's too easy.

897
01:11:45,439 --> 01:11:46,982
I got one.

898
01:11:47,941 --> 01:11:50,944
I'm seven years old and my dad
takes me to Yankee Stadium.

899
01:11:50,944 --> 01:11:52,655
My first game.

900
01:11:52,946 --> 01:11:56,450
We're going in this long,
dark tunnel underneath the stands.

901
01:11:56,450 --> 01:12:00,496
I'm holding his hand and we come up
out of the tunnel into the light.

902
01:12:01,705 --> 01:12:06,335
It was huge. How green
the grass was. Brown the dirt.

903
01:12:07,211 --> 01:12:10,172
And that great green
copper roof. Remember?

904
01:12:10,339 --> 01:12:14,718
We had a black-and-white TV, so this
was the first game I ever saw in colour.

905
01:12:15,010 --> 01:12:17,262
I sat there the whole game
next to my Dad.

906
01:12:17,262 --> 01:12:19,682
He taught me how to keep score.

907
01:12:20,265 --> 01:12:22,184
Mickey hit one out.

908
01:12:22,768 --> 01:12:25,646
- Good day.
- I still have the programme.

909
01:12:27,439 --> 01:12:30,567
All right, what was
the worst day you ever had?

910
01:12:32,611 --> 01:12:36,073
Worst day. A couple of years ago,
Barbara finds a lump.

911
01:12:36,115 --> 01:12:38,117
- What?
- Jesus.

912
01:12:38,117 --> 01:12:41,286
- It scared the shit out of me.
- You never said anything.

913
01:12:41,286 --> 01:12:45,207
Yeah, well, it turned out to be
nothing. But that whole day was...

914
01:12:47,209 --> 01:12:49,628
- Yeah, but that was a good day.
- How?

915
01:12:49,628 --> 01:12:54,258
- Because it turned out to be nothing.
- Yeah, but the day until then was horrible.

916
01:12:54,633 --> 01:12:56,635
Yeah, but it came out good.

917
01:12:56,635 --> 01:13:00,639
You're a real "the glass is half-empty"
kind of a guy, you know that?

918
01:13:00,639 --> 01:13:03,058
I don't know how Barbara can stand it.

919
01:13:03,058 --> 01:13:04,393
Yeah.

920
01:13:04,560 --> 01:13:07,062
All right. I got one.
My best day.

921
01:13:07,062 --> 01:13:09,231
The one about Arlene
and that loose step?

922
01:13:09,231 --> 01:13:11,317
No.
No, my wedding day.

