01:30:03,078 --> 01:30:05,581
- How would I see it?
- To see it, you need a TV.

1148
01:30:05,581 --> 01:30:08,459
Shut up. Just shut up.
He doesn't get it!

1149
01:30:09,043 --> 01:30:13,839
He'll never get it. It's been four hours.
The cows can tape something by now.

1150
01:30:14,048 --> 01:30:16,175
Forget about it, please!

1151
01:30:18,427 --> 01:30:21,889
- How do you do the clock?
- You're dead. You are dead!

1152
01:30:44,703 --> 01:30:46,413
Yah! Yah!
Yah!

1153
01:30:47,206 --> 01:30:49,792
Let's go. Come on, Norman.
Keep up.

1154
01:30:50,709 --> 01:30:53,629
Norman, stay with the class.
Come on, boy.

1155
01:30:54,421 --> 01:30:55,923
Aw, shit.

1156
01:30:56,423 --> 01:30:59,343
- What do we do now?
- Like I should know?

1157
01:30:59,343 --> 01:31:02,930
- Come on, let's keep the herd together.
- Yeah, let's go.

1158
01:31:03,347 --> 01:31:07,059
Let's go, Norman. Norman,
what are you? Gene Kelly? Let's go.

1159
01:31:21,365 --> 01:31:23,617
Easy, boy.
Whoa! Easy, boy.

1160
01:31:25,244 --> 01:31:26,996
Go!
Go, go, go!

1161
01:31:37,715 --> 01:31:40,217
We're doing great guys.
We're driving'em.

1162
01:31:40,217 --> 01:31:43,679
That's perfect. We're lost,
but we're making good time.

1163
01:31:43,721 --> 01:31:46,390
This is the way, guys.
I can feel it.

1164
01:32:04,241 --> 01:32:06,744
- Is there a way around?
- That could be a hundred miles.

1165
01:32:06,744 --> 01:32:09,872
- It could take days.
- Is this supposed to be here?

1166
01:32:09,872 --> 01:32:13,334
There's probably an easy place
to cross but we missed it.

1167
01:32:13,334 --> 01:32:16,253
- This could be the easy place!
- Oh, God.

1168
01:32:17,129 --> 01:32:21,842
We did the best we could. Let's just leave
the herd and get the hell outta here, huh?

1169
01:32:22,217 --> 01:32:24,845
No.
A cowboy doesn't leave his herd.

1170
01:32:25,763 --> 01:32:28,307
You are a sporting-goods salesman!

1171
01:32:31,143 --> 01:32:32,686
Not today.

1172
01:32:38,442 --> 01:32:40,027
Easy... OK.

1173
01:32:41,862 --> 01:32:44,740
I started this...
and I'm gonna finish it.

1174
01:32:45,783 --> 01:32:47,743
I'm gonna finish it.

1175
01:32:54,750 --> 01:32:58,170
It's fast, but it's not deep.
Come on, bring'em down.

1176
01:32:59,630 --> 01:33:01,715
Come on!
Let's go!

1177
01:33:08,639 --> 01:33:10,099
Oh, God.

1178
01:33:34,123 --> 01:33:36,208
Come on, move!
Move it!

1179
01:33:44,216 --> 01:33:46,260
Move it, now.
Come on.

1180
01:33:48,095 --> 01:33:49,430
Whoa!

1181
01:33:51,557 --> 01:33:52,891
Shit.

1182
01:34:08,365 --> 01:34:12,286
Come on, boys! Come on, now.
Move it! Moo cow!

1183
01:34:12,661 --> 01:34:14,580
Go, baby!
Go, baby!

1184
01:34:14,830 --> 01:34:18,751
Hey, Phil. I'm 39 and
I'm saying "moo cow" in a river.

1185
01:34:19,627 --> 01:34:21,587
Do you believe this?

1186
01:34:22,129 --> 01:34:24,089
- We did it!
- Hey!

1187
01:34:39,897 --> 01:34:41,190
Yah!

1188
01:34:45,361 --> 01:34:46,945
Here we go!

1189
01:34:52,326 --> 01:34:53,744
Norman!

1190
01:34:55,454 --> 01:34:56,914
Oh, God.

1191
01:35:31,949 --> 01:35:33,283
Whoa!

1192
01:35:43,043 --> 01:35:44,461
Norman!

1193
01:35:46,964 --> 01:35:48,382
Norman!

1194
01:35:51,135 --> 01:35:52,886
Norman!
Norman!

1195
01:35:54,430 --> 01:35:55,848
Norman!

1196
01:35:59,810 --> 01:36:01,520
Got you.
Help!

1197
01:36:02,813 --> 01:36:04,690
Oh, my God.
Mitch!

1198
01:36:04,732 --> 01:36:07,359
- Hey, Ed!
- Help! Help me!

1199
01:36:10,654 --> 01:36:12,072
Oh, no.

1200
01:36:17,244 --> 01:36:18,620
Mitch!

1201
01:36:37,139 --> 01:36:38,641
Oh, shit.

1202
01:37:12,466 --> 01:37:14,051
I'm coming!

1203
01:37:14,969 --> 01:37:16,553
I'm coming!

1204
01:37:24,269 --> 01:37:26,105
Come on!
Come on!

1205
01:37:26,855 --> 01:37:28,691
Come on!
Come on!

1206
01:37:45,958 --> 01:37:48,460
Gimme your hand.
Gimme your hand.

1207
01:37:55,801 --> 01:37:59,888
You're crazy. You talk about me,
but you're crazy.

1208
01:38:01,473 --> 01:38:04,810
- You coulda been killed!
- We almost lost you, pal.

1209
01:38:14,111 --> 01:38:15,696
Nice catch.

1210
01:38:17,614 --> 01:38:20,451
It was like Mays in the '54 World Series.

1211
01:38:21,410 --> 01:38:23,620
- Vic Wertz.
- Vic Wertz.

1212
01:39:40,531 --> 01:39:42,992
- Let's bring'em in.
- Yee-ha!

1213
01:39:53,210 --> 01:39:55,337
Great gobs of gooseshit!

1214
01:39:56,422 --> 01:39:58,382
It's them!
Ira! Ira!

1215
01:40:26,452 --> 01:40:28,078
Yahoo!

1216
01:40:49,975 --> 01:40:51,310
Whoo!

1217
01:41:02,404 --> 01:41:04,073
Whoo!
Yee-ha!

1218
01:41:12,164 --> 01:41:13,540
Yahoo!

1219
01:41:15,501 --> 01:41:16,877
Yahoo!

1220
01:41:22,091 --> 01:41:23,884
Way to go, guys.

1221
01:41:26,387 --> 01:41:28,013
- Hi.
- Hi.

1222
01:41:35,187 --> 01:41:37,022
Oh, Lordy, Lordy.

1223
01:41:41,443 --> 01:41:45,197
- Here's your herd.
- I'm as happy as a puppy with two peters.

1224
01:41:45,990 --> 01:41:48,200
We had a search party out lookin' for you.

1225
01:41:48,200 --> 01:41:51,286
- They didn't find us.
- Un-by-God-believable.

1226
01:41:52,204 --> 01:41:54,873
Bunch o' tenderfeet
bringin' in a herd.

1227
01:41:54,873 --> 01:41:58,419
Two weeks ago, you boys were as
worthless as henshit on a pump handle.

1228
01:41:58,419 --> 01:42:00,212
Look at you now!

1229
01:42:00,337 --> 01:42:03,257
- I'm givin' your money back!

1230
01:42:04,133 --> 01:42:06,302
Now you're talking, Clay.

1231
01:42:06,760 --> 01:42:10,723
Instead of the money, you think
my dad and I could come back and...

1232
01:42:10,764 --> 01:42:13,767
...take the cattle back to New Mexico?
- Really, son?

1233
01:42:13,767 --> 01:42:17,438
Ordinarily, that'd be great,
but this herd's not goin' back.

1234
01:42:18,105 --> 01:42:19,106
What do you mean?

1235
01:42:19,106 --> 01:42:22,151
I'm gettin' top dollar
from the meat company.

1236
01:42:23,110 --> 01:42:27,031
- You mean these cows are...
- I thought you just moved'em around?

1237
01:42:27,031 --> 01:42:30,701
Usually do, but prices are
sky high, and I can't pass it up.

1238
01:42:36,582 --> 01:42:40,294
Look, folks, it's not like
any of'em have a lot to live for.

1239
01:42:40,794 --> 01:42:42,796
They don't have much of a life, anyway.

1240
01:42:42,796 --> 01:42:46,300
- Phil doesn't, but we wouldn't eat him.
- That's right.

1241
01:42:46,550 --> 01:42:50,262
This is our business, son.
This is not an endangered species.

1242
01:42:52,181 --> 01:42:54,183
It's what these animals are bred for.

1243
01:42:54,183 --> 01:42:58,604
All that meat under Cellophane in the
store, where do you think it comes from?

1244
01:42:58,937 --> 01:43:01,231
Come on, fellas.
Just relax.

1245
01:43:01,357 --> 01:43:03,400
You done real good, cowboys.

1246
01:43:03,400 --> 01:43:05,361
Let's get some grub.

1247
01:43:22,503 --> 01:43:24,546
These cows trusted us.

1248
01:43:25,297 --> 01:43:28,175
They trusted us?
They don't even know us!

1249
01:43:28,801 --> 01:43:31,762
They followed us
because we yelled "Yah".

1250
01:43:31,804 --> 01:43:33,555
They're cattle.

1251
01:44:25,858 --> 01:44:27,192
What?

1252
01:45:05,272 --> 01:45:08,025
I've gotta stop bein' a schmuck.

1253
01:45:08,317 --> 01:45:10,736
You know, you were right, Mitch.

1254
01:45:10,736 --> 01:45:14,031
My life is a "do over".
It's time to get started.

1255
01:45:17,326 --> 01:45:19,203
I hope I can help.

1256
01:45:21,330 --> 01:45:23,290
I'm gonna go home...

1257
01:45:23,832 --> 01:45:25,834
...and I'm gonna get Kim pregnant.

1258
01:45:25,834 --> 01:45:29,296
- I hope I can help.
- Oh, Mitchy the Kid's in trouble.

1259
01:45:32,967 --> 01:45:35,094
- What about you?
- Hm?

1260
01:45:35,469 --> 01:45:38,806
- You gonna be OK?
- Yeah. Cos I know what he meant.

1261
01:45:39,473 --> 01:45:42,142
- Who?
- Curly. I know what this is.

1262
01:45:42,977 --> 01:45:45,479
- What?
- That's what you have to figure out.

1263
01:45:45,479 --> 01:45:47,982
- I'm gonna deck you, pal.
- No, that's what it is.

1264
01:45:47,982 --> 01:45:51,485
It's different for everybody.
It's whatever's most important to you.

1265
01:45:51,485 --> 01:45:55,531
For me, when I was in the river,
I was only thinkin' about one thing.

1266
01:45:55,990 --> 01:45:58,617
All that other stuff just went away.

1267
01:45:58,993 --> 01:46:01,662
Only one thing really mattered to me.

1268
01:46:02,496 --> 01:46:04,832
- Dad!
- Daddy, you're home!

1269
01:46:09,586 --> 01:46:11,171
I love you.

1270
01:46:12,589 --> 01:46:14,591
These faces.
I missed these faces.

1271
01:46:14,591 --> 01:46:18,012
- We missed you too, Daddy.
- It's no fun without you.

1272
01:46:18,595 --> 01:46:20,347
Hey, buckaroos.

1273
01:46:22,099 --> 01:46:24,518
- Next year, the North Pole.
- What?

1274
01:46:24,518 --> 01:46:27,938
We hire dog sleds and follow
the same route as Admiral Byrd.

1275
01:46:27,938 --> 01:46:29,148
Uh-huh.

1276
01:46:29,148 --> 01:46:31,525
Next Tuesday, coffee and cake.

1277
01:46:32,568 --> 01:46:33,485
Better.

1278
01:46:33,485 --> 01:46:35,029
Come here.

1279
01:46:39,450 --> 01:46:41,535
Hey, Phil!
You need a ride?

1280
01:46:41,535 --> 01:46:43,662
No, thanks.
I got a cab.

1281
01:46:59,136 --> 01:47:02,097
- So, how are you?
- Good. Things are good.

1282
01:47:04,099 --> 01:47:05,976
Look what I found.

1283
01:47:07,436 --> 01:47:09,813
Mm, that's nice.
Where was it?

1284
01:47:10,439 --> 01:47:14,693
Colorado. I mean, it's always
the last place you look.

1285
01:47:16,528 --> 01:47:18,739
Mitch, I've been thinking.

1286
01:47:19,531 --> 01:47:22,534
If you really hate your job,
why don't you get out of there?

1287
01:47:22,534 --> 01:47:25,954
- We'll be all right.
- No. I'm not gonna quit my job.

1288
01:47:27,081 --> 01:47:30,751
I'm just gonna do it better.
I'm gonna do everything better.

1289
01:47:31,627 --> 01:47:33,212
Everything?

1290
01:47:49,520 --> 01:47:50,813
See?

1291
01:47:51,814 --> 01:47:54,650
- Oh, I missed you.
- I missed you, too.

1292
01:47:55,818 --> 01:47:57,319
Let's go home.

1293
01:47:57,319 --> 01:48:00,698
Today... is my best day.

1294
01:48:06,120 --> 01:48:07,705
Mr Robbins?

1295
01:48:08,580 --> 01:48:10,416
Yeah, right here.

1296
01:48:11,667 --> 01:48:13,377
This is great.

1297
01:48:14,878 --> 01:48:17,089
- There you go.
- Thanks.

1298
01:48:17,381 --> 01:48:20,342
- What, did you get a dog?
- We got a dog?!

1299
01:48:20,342 --> 01:48:22,970
- All right!
- Come on, little man.

1300
01:48:26,265 --> 01:48:28,434
Everyone, this is Norman.

1301
01:48:31,145 --> 01:48:33,230
- It's a cow.
- Uh-uh.

1302
01:48:33,605 --> 01:48:35,607
He's a calf, actually.

1303
01:48:35,607 --> 01:48:38,360
Mitch!
You're gonna put him in the van?

1304
01:48:39,945 --> 01:48:41,864
Oh, yeah.
And then the den.

1305
01:48:41,864 --> 01:48:45,951
- You're not gonna take him home.
- See, kids, he just said "Hello".

1306
01:48:46,869 --> 01:48:50,372
Just for a little while.
Then we'll put him in a petting zoo...

1307
01:48:50,372 --> 01:48:53,334
...so he can be with your mother.
- Mitch!

1308
01:48:54,877 --> 01:48:57,254
I'm kidding!
I'm just kidding.

1309
01:49:03,385 --> 01:49:06,472
- OK, seat belts, Norman. Seat belts.
- Mitch!

1310
01:49:06,889 --> 01:49:10,225
I hope you went to the bathroom.
We got a long ride.

1311
01:49:10,392 --> 01:49:12,603
- Mitch!
- Let's go home.

